race.comment: SHEZA ALIBI (12) clearly looks the horse to beat. She stuck on very well first up behind subsequent Coolmore winner Tentyris, looking well placed in the G3 Vanity at Flemington and duly saluting after squeezing through a narrow gap, coming away to win well once clear. Can't see 1600m being an issue off that, she'll just need another gap from barrier one if they don't ride her aggressively to lead. BURMA STAR (2) is a danger. He came down from Sydney and won the Listed Amanda Elliott impressively at 1400m on Cup day, coming from well back to score. Gets a nice draw here to track the favourite and can win. CENTU CAVADDI (9) might be the blowout. He was too bad to be true in a strange race here last time, the run prior when flying home at 1400m is good form. TAGLINE (5) was close up behind BURMA STAR last time and that effort has him in the mix.
